external_knowledge:
- Energy data refers to information about energy consumption and production; 
- Quality checks are evaluations of the accuracy and reliability of the energy data; 
- Regional reference prices are prices used for reference in a specific region; 
- Settlement dates are dates when energy usage is settled or finalized; 
- Total demand refers to the total amount of energy required; 
- Usernames are unique identifiers for users who perform quality checks.

- The query assumes that the data quality score is a measure of the accuracy of the forecasting models; 
- A higher data quality score indicates better model performance; 
- The `RANK()` function is used to rank the forecasting models, with the model having the highest average data quality score ranked as 1; 
- The settlement date refers to the date and time when the energy demand data was recorded.
